## One-on-One Chatting/Group Chats

### Create Conversation

In table `_Conversation`, the default ACL authority requires master key to create.

```sh
curl -X POST \
  -H "X-LC-Id: {{appid}}" \
  -H "X-LC-Key: {{masterkey}},master" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name":"My First Conversation", "m": ["BillGates", "SteveJobs"], "unique": true}' \
  https://{{host}}/1.2/rtm/conversations
```

The above instance will create an elementary conversation, including two initial participants having client ID 'BillGates' and 'SteveJobs'. A success creation will return the objectId. Namely , the rtm message ID. The client terminal can send message with this code. The created conversations can be queried from table `_Conversation`. Strings in conversations can refer to the [Conversation](realtime_v2.html#Conversation) in Realtime Message - guide. Inputting `"unique": true` will ensure the uniqueness of the conversation.

return
```
{"objectId"=>"5a5d7432c3422b31ed845e75", "createdAt"=>"2018-01-16T03:40:32.814Z"}
```

The only distinction between One-on-One Chatting and Group Chats is the number of the clients. The two share the same API.

